article.headline: Tennessee Tech 86, Bradley 84
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Anthony Fisher made a layup at the buzzer to lift Tennessee Tech to an 86-84 victory Wednesday over Bradley. Bradley's Jeremy Crouch had tied the game 84-84 on a jumper with 23 seconds left. Tennessee Tech (3-2) rallied from six points down in the final 4:31. Bradley (5-2) led 76-70 on two free throws by J.J. Tauai. Tech had blown a 12-point second-half lead, 52-40 with 16:49 left. Fisher led Tech with 20 points, Bolton Rivers had 19, Amadi McKenzie 16 and Rashaud Nixon 11. Seven of Rivers' points came in the last 3:23. The Golden Eagles hit 53.4 percent from the field to 49.2 percent for Bradley, which played its first road game of the season. Zach Andrews led the Braves with 22 points and 14 rebounds. Daniel Ruffin and Crouch scored 13 each and Will Franklin had 10. The Golden Eagles led 41-32 at the half.
